@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

@{MS "Introduction"}

IRCom is a driver packet which allows to process IR signals. It's possible to
send and receive ir signals. This allows to remote control your computer and to
control external devices by using the computer as remote control.@{par}

This packet contains several small tools for custom usage. Some external
applications are supporting IRCom drivers. These are Meridian, MMKeyboard and
IRComRemote.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "System Requirenents"

@{MS "System Requirements"}

At least OS2 is required. Some features and drivers require OS3.x or higher. MorphOS is also supported.@{par}

Of course you need one of the IR Devices supported by this packet.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Features"

@{MS "Features"}

 ° Easy configuration@{par}

 ° online and bubble help.@{par}

 ° MUI GUI.@{par}

 ° Multi language support.@{par}

 ° Several hardware drivers and their needed Poseidon USB Classes included.@{par}

@endnode
