@node "Buglist" "Buglist"

@{MS "Buglist"}

@{MT "MorphOS 1.4 bedingte Probleme"}

The UHCI USB driver available with MorphOS isn't working correct.@{par}

This effects only the IRTrans adapter, which rejects to work on MOS.@{par}

Please also note that IR interfaces without integrated circuits can't be used on
the serial port. The type of hardware doesn't matter. The problem is that there
is no software interface to handle single serial lines. These interfaces are
lame anyway, because it would reguire to disable interrupts which would kill
system multitask to ensure proper ir stream sampling. So the rule is: No chip
- no good!.@{par}

@endnode
